{
  "_meta": {
    "purpose": "Illustrative scenarios for platform worked examples: how much a worker grossed and what they spent earning it. These are NOT tax figures. Every rate applied to them — the 72.5c mileage rate, the 80% gig-driver phone business-use share, SE tax, brackets — comes from the verified dataset. What lives here is only the shape of the example.",
    "why": "The platform entries in legacy/data/config.json carry incomeType, fees and a list of deduction categories, but no example income and no usage figures. A worked example needs both. Inventing a tax rate would break ground rule 2; choosing a plausible scenario to apply verified rates to does not — but it is a choice, so it is recorded here in the open rather than buried in a template.",
    "rules": [
      "Round, obviously-illustrative numbers. These are not survey data and must never be presented as typical earnings.",
      "Pages must describe them as an example, never as what a worker on this platform earns.",
      "Any figure that is a tax rate, threshold or limit belongs in the verified dataset, not here."
    ],
    "coverage": "15 platforms. Driving platforms carry a mileage figure; selling and creator platforms do not, because their deduction stack is fees, cost of goods and equipment rather than the car. Every scenario is a round illustrative shape chosen to sit in a plausible range — none of it is survey data and pages must never present it as typical earnings.",
    "sellerNote": "cogsPct is an illustrative share of gross that goes on inventory or materials — a business shape, not a tax figure. homeOfficeSqFt feeds the verified simplified-method rate of $5 per square foot up to 300, from selfEmploymentDeductions.homeOffice.",
    "categoryNote": "Scenarios are chosen so each CATEGORY has a distinct deduction shape, because that is what the category pages are about: mileage-led for drivers, tools and materials for services, equipment and workspace for creators, cost of goods and fees for sellers, cleaning and repairs for hosts."
  },
